Energetics of Dnipropetrovsk started a unique program to save... nests of ashtrays
In the old days, to lead to the court of the aist, the peasants on a high pole installed a wheel from a cart, and a heavy nest held well on it.
Such special supports have not been put for a long time, so the oaks loved the pillars of power lines - interwoven branches rely on wires, so that the real house is reliable.
Grandmother Anya, near whose house in the village of Ivanovka Petrikovsky district for twenty years lives a real family, began to notice how the nest settles, despite all the efforts of its inhabitants.
Birds lay new branches from above, and the lower layer has already slipped between the wires, it is about to collapse.
Of course, unfortunately, the family of aphists, who every year nestled in the yard, brought out and fed three or four chicks during the summer, but also do not want to stay without light.
As soon as the birds flew to the warm edges, Grandmother Anya called the Tsarichansky REC, which owns the support.
I didn’t expect them to react so quickly.
When our specialists arrived in Ivanovka, they were surprised that the nest still holds, - said the technical director of DTEK "Dneproblenergo" Sergey Berezovsky.
Corrosion began on the wires, which were, in fact, already inside the socket, weighing 150 - 200 kilograms.
At any moment, the birds could die from electrical discharge.
Local residents also risked losing their light due to damage to the wires.
Therefore, the linear mounters began the operation to save the nest, and this is not the first time in our practice.
The scientists-ornithologists from Dnepropetrovsk National University, who developed a scheme for the transfer of the nest, helped.
They also conducted trainings for the employees of the district networks.
The famous Dnipropetrovsk ornithologist Alexander Ponomarenko advised energy engineers at all stages of the reconstruction of the nests.
To begin with, it was estimated that there are more than 50 true "apartments" in the area in a state of emergency.
For their reconstruction, special metal platforms resembling a funnel were welded.
The base was braided with velvet branches, and then the old nest was moved there.
According to experts, it is enough to lay old branches as a basis for the birds to recognize the nest and return to it.
After that, they will build their own homes.
A month ago, the first nest was reconstructed in the village of Peschanka in Novomoskovsky district.
A new reinforced concrete pillar was placed next to the electrical base and a platform with an old, already inhabited nest was placed on it.
The entire operation cost energy workers nine thousand hryvnia.
And the other day the same new settlement took place in the village of Ivanovka Petrikovsky district in the yard of grandmother Ani.
Here the platform was fixed in the same place, just lifted over the wires.
Ornithologists are confident that cautious, conservative birds will not even notice in the spring that their "apartment" has undergone major repairs.
By the end of the year, the same reconstruction awaits four more nests in the Pokrovsk and Tsarichan districts of Dnipropetrovsk.
By the way, while some save rare birds, others mercilessly kill them.
The other day, the whole region flew sad news - in the village of Ust-Kamenka Apostolovsky district, on the day of the opening of the hunt for pheasants, poachers for entertainment shot the swan family, who lived in the local pond.
Noble birds were not afraid of people at all - the locals fed them and did not offend them.
When the villagers heard the gunshots, they rushed to the pond, four beautiful swans were already lying dead on the water.
Now the employees of the Apostolic Rayon of the police find out who shot the birds recorded in the Red Book.
