How quickly such a change is realized will vary depending on the airline, FAU administrator Michael Huerta said at a press conference.
Airlines will have to show the FAU how their aircraft comply with the new guidelines and that they are updating their training manuals for flight crew members and setup rules to comply with the new guidelines.
The FAU said it had already received plans from some airlines to expand the use of portable electronic devices on planes.
